The reason why we are only now feeling its effects, even though the use of asbestos has been illegal for years (all types of asbestos were finally banned by law in 1999), is that it usually takes several decades for mesothelioma to develop.
The disaster in the form of mesothelioma is not just affecting construction industry veterans.
Asbestos has been, and in many cases still is, present in the homes in which we live, in the offices where we work, in the schools where we learn, and in the shops where we shop.
Thus, mesothelioma does not respect social class, wealth, occupation or age.
Privileged bastions, from London department stores to public schools, are no shelter.
Parliament is also full of asbestos.
